pageContext.claim: “From Cedar Rapids, where I made my last speech prior to the election. What a place, 32,000 people. I said, ‘I'm going to win tomorrow.’”
pageContext.analysis: Trump got the city, state and attendance numbers wrong. His last speech prior to the 2016 election was in Grand Rapids, Mich., not Cedar Rapids, Iowa.  The venue (in Michigan) held more than 4,000 people, not anywhere near 32,000.
